The Commission will unpack evidence relating to the Free State Asbestos Project from the province's Head of the Human Settlements Department Nthimotse Mokhesi. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry remains focussed on the Free State. On Monday, it will look into an asbestos project in that province. It will look at the testimony of the Head of Human Settlements, Nthimotse Mokhesi. The Commission will also hear more evidence related to the R1-billion Free State Housing Project.